<subSubSection id="29BF6EFB5FC88B5892642230B084F6AF" pageId="0" pageNumber="55" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="9190EE26183500DD3F0403E9B9215218" pageId="0" pageNumber="55">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="5E843F709DBE17C55D90FC749089BBC1" pageId="0" pageNumber="55">
Pileus vinaceous to brown, pores whitish to pinkish at maturity, vinaceous context; longitudinally fribrillose stipe; basidiospores (10) 11-17 (-21) 
<normalizedToken id="D600C7E63A713DB5BE5DA4E2DA4B48CB" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
4-5 (-7) 
<normalizedToken id="3DA18481C42A9645CA08E07C3D3D0147" originalValue="µm">µm</normalizedToken>
, slightly verrucose to cracked, fusoid to cylindrical; pleurocystidia ventricose-rostrate to fusoid, cheilocystidia sphaeropedunculate.
</paragraph>
<caption id="A57AA69CE1C6B957EB8D5F52C37D953B" doi="10.3897/mycokeys.88.73951.figure3" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/665980" pageId="0" pageNumber="55" start="Figure 3" startId="F3">
