<subSubSection id="AB0D90387A695B7D56E654474D70620A" pageId="0" pageNumber="55" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="D8D054B48C5E0FE34C2F334CE91D55BF" pageId="0" pageNumber="55">Etymology.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="09C853650FB3430DC94D2D3B3DAD483F" pageId="0" pageNumber="55">
The name refers to the colour of the pileus, from the Latin &quot; 
<emphasis id="F592E21D4A26DB546FDB2713DFCF5F65" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="55">vinosus</emphasis>
&quot; vinaceous when young and &quot; 
<emphasis id="DD19C445A2939B37140654434FA51145" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="55">brunneus</emphasis>
&quot; brown when mature.
</paragraph>
<caption id="056AD4614747C8C3B2C996513363E9AF" doi="10.3897/mycokeys.88.73951.figure5" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/665982" pageId="0" pageNumber="55" start="Figure 5" startId="F5">
